,743) of the showcase he was offered, amid allegations of cheating.<ref name=\"Kniess\">{{cite magazine|last=Jones|first=Chris|title=TV's Crowning Moment of Awesome|url=http://www.esquire.com/news-politics/a7922/price-is-right-perfect-bid-0810/|magazine=Esquire|date=July 11, 2010|accessdate=March 7, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! 27\n| After over eighteen years, [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] drops children's programming. Its final children's programming block, [[4Kids TV]], goes off the air, and [[4Kids Entertainment]] directs its programming to [[The CW4Kids]], the block it programs for [[The CW]]. [[4Kids TV]] would later launch as an online-only website on the same day.\n|-\n! 29\n|After four years, [[Adult Swim]] adds an hour to its operating day (the block, which used to begin at 11:00&nbsp;p.m., now starts at 10:00&nbsp;p.m. and runs to 6:00&nbsp;a.m.)\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|31\n|[[Time Warner Cable]] and [[Bright House Networks]] announce they are no longer carrying [[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]] channels unless they come to an agreement with Viacom. They come to an agreement at the last minute.\n|-\n|[[NBC Weather Plus]] is shut down.\n|}\n\n==Programs==\n\n===Debuts (including scheduled)===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Date || Title || Network\n|-\n|January 6\n|''[[Biz Kid$]]''\n|[[PBS Kids Go!]]\n|-\n|January 9\n|''[[Ghost Hunters International]]''\n|[[Syfy|Sci Fi]]\n|-\n|January 13\n|''[[Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles]]''\n|[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n|-\n|January 20\n|''[[Breaking Bad]]''\n|[[AMC (TV network)|AMC]]\n|-\n|January 23\n|''[[The Moment of Truth (U.S. game show)|The Moment of Truth]]''\n|[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n|-\n|January 25\n|''[[Gone Country (TV series)|Gone Country]]''\n|[[Country Music Television|CMT]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|January 28\n|''[[Captain Flamingo]]''\n|[[Jetix]]\n|-\n|''[[In Treatment (U.S. TV series)|In Treatment]]''\n|[[HBO]]\n|-\n|January 31\n|''[[Eli Stone]]''\n|[[American Broadcasting Com