ame show host (''[[Beat the Clock]]'', ''[[Concentration (game show)|Concentration]]'')\n|-\n|October 25\n|[[Anne Pressly]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26\n| Anchorwoman and special assignment reporter for [[KATV]]/[[Little Rock, Arkansas]]\n|-\n|November 4\n|[[Michael Crichton]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|66\n| Author and screenwriter (''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'')\n|-\n|November 11\n|[[Herb Score]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|75\n| Baseball player and TV/Radio play-by-play announcer for the [[Cleveland Indians]]\n|-\n|December 1\n|[[Paul Benedict]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|70\n| Character actor, writer and director (''[[The Jeffersons]]'', ''[[Sesame Street]]'')\n|-\n|December 5\n|[[Beverly Garland]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|82\n| Actress, singer and businesswoman (''[[My Three Sons]]'', ''[[Scarecrow and Mrs. King]]'')\n|-\n|December 8\n|[[Robert Prosky]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|77\n| Actor (''[[Hill Street Blues]]'')\n|-\n|December 12\n|[[Van Johnson]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|92\n| Actor and singer (''[[Batman (TV series)|Batman]]'', ''[[Here's Lucy]]'', ''[[The Pied Piper of Hamelin (1957 film)|The Pied Piper of Hamelin (1957 television film)]]'')\n|-\n|December 13\n|[[Maddie Blaustein]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|48\n| Voice actress (''[[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'', ''[[Yu-Gi-Oh!]]'', ''[[Dinosaur King]]'')\n|-\n|December 18\n|[[Majel Barrett]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|76\n| Actress (''[[Star Trek: The Original Series]]'')\n|-\n|December 25\n|[[Eartha Kitt]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|81\n| Actress, dancer and singer (''[[Batman (TV series)|Batman]]'', ''[[The Emperor's New School]]'')\n|}\n\n{{Years in TV by country|2008}}\n{{Years in television}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2008 in the United States]]\n* [[List of American films of 2008]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.nypost.com/seven/12012008/tv/and_thats_the_way_it_is_141620.htm NYPost]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2008 I