oralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_1987.txt|publisher=[[Electoral Calculus]]|accessdate=18 October 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015054243/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_1987.txt|archivedate=15 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politicsresources.net/area/uk/ge87/ge87index.htm|title=Politics Resources|date=11 June 1987|work=Election 1987|publisher=Politics Resources|accessdate=17 September 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520233245/http://www.politicsresources.net/area/uk/ge87/ge87index.htm|archive-date=20 May 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n|party      = Labour Party (UK)\n|candidate  = [[Terry Davis (politician)|Terry Davis]]\n|votes  = 19,872\n|percentage  = 48.7\n|change  = {{increase}} 1.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n|candidate  = Stephen Eyre\n|votes  = 15,083\n|percentage  = 37.0\n|change  = {{increase}} 1.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n|candidate  = Kenneth Hardeman\n|votes  = 5,868\n|percentage  = 14.4\n|change  = {{decrease}} 1.5\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n|votes  = 4,789\n|percentage  = 11.7\n|change  = {{decrease}}0.7\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n|votes  = 40,823\n|percentage  = 68.9\n|change  = {{increase}} 1.3\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n|winner     = Labour Party (UK)\n|swing      = {{decrease}} 0.3\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin |\n|title=[[1983 United Kingdom general election|General election 1983]]: Birmingham Hodge Hill<ref name=electoralcalculus1983>{{cite web|title=Election Data 1983|url=http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_1983.txt|publisher=[[Electoral Calculus]]|accessdate=18 October 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015054231/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_1983.txt|archivedate=15 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politicsresources.